Winner is @thefairbanksfam 

🎉GIVEAWAY🎉 
There’s nothing more priceless than your photo and video memories.  That’s why I am so excited to team up with @urlifemedia to offer an amazing GIVEAWAY!!!!

I take a ton of photos and videos, and I am sure you do, too. I always procrastinate pulling them together into videos because the process is time consuming and overwhelming.  That’s where my new favorite indulgence @URLIFEMEDIA comes in.  They have Hollywood producers on staff to turn your footage into amazing memories.  You don’t have to worry about wasting time going through your videos and choosing the best footage, they do it for you 😳 with prices starting as low as $75. 

When I got our completed Christmas video back, I heard things I didn’t even realize had happened (listen closely for Savannah saying “that’s weird” when Santa drives a car). The film captures our family and holiday celebration perfectly and it will help the kids remember our quarantine Christmas for many years to come.  After you’ve seen, it I wonder who will want to have Christmas at our house next year 😂? 

We want to share this experience with someone else by giving away one custom 2.5 minute Hollywood level URLIFE movie (value $595). 

To enter 
1.Follow @bennetttriplets and @urlifemedia on IG.
2.Comment below and tell me what your first URLIFE project will be about (my next project is going to be a fun day trip we took to the Safari Park) it could be anything - a previous vacation, year in review, birthday. . . really anything.
3. Don’t let your friends miss out.  Tag a couple of busy moms who would love to win. If you share this post in your story and tag us, you’ll get another entry. 

We’ll go live next Saturday 2/8 and the triplets will draw a winner.  We will continue working with @urlifemedia, so I will have discount codes coming up and so much more!

node.text:
I posted the comparison photo of the triplets in their graduation shirts the other day.  Every year I add what they want to be when they grow up to the back and am excited to see their interests change as they get older. 

After I snapped the photos they all wanted to ride their scooters.  I couldn’t stand how cute they all looked in those giant tees racing up and down the sidewalk.  One minute I look at them and think they’re still babies and the next I can’t believe how grown up they are.  Here they were all just enjoying the moment, being young and completely  carefree…. those are the moments I want to lock in my memory and never let go of.

node.text:
Last weekend I got brave and stuck my iPhone in the water 😱. I have a GoPro but for some reason it’s never charged when we need it to be.🤷🏻‍♀️

I’ve been working with the kids to keep their 👀 on the camera when they’re under the water.  Savannah came downstairs this morning and wanted to spend some time in the pool with me 🎥 her.  This is a screen shot of a slow-mo video I took earlier today (swipe for the video). We did a little playing in Lightroom and I think it’s a pretty amazing shot.

I was chatting with a friend this morning and she said the triplets were so beautiful and I gave her my usual response – “Thank you!  I like to joke that when I was pregnant I prayed for beautiful babies.  Looking back I should have prayed for babies that slept through the night or ones that listened” but this time I followed it up with “to be honest a triplet pregnancy was so risky I really just hoped that one would survive.”

That got me thinking a lot about hopes and dreams. 

I have shared so much with you over the years… but to fill in new followers a quick run-down:
Lost my mom at age 5 ⬇
Lost my Grandma at  10 ⬇
Started working at 14 ⬇
Exchange student at 16 🙌🏻
Moved out at age 18 ⬇
Hypothyroid at 19 ⬇
Married at 27 🙌🏻
Infertility at age 35 ⬇
Lost baby #1 (full term) age 36 ⬇
Lost baby #2 at age 37 ⬇
IVF at age 38 ⬇
Delivered healthy triplets at 39 🙌🏻
Bought a business at age 42 🙌🏻
Finally lost the weight (or at least enough of it 😆) at 43 🙌🏻

I was never really raised to dream big.  I shielded my heart from disappointment by anticipating failure.  But what if you could have everything you ever wanted?  Would you think differently?  I had learned to expect loss, so all I dared to hope for was one baby – yet I got 3 (and they were pretty just like I wished for 😂). I was blown away.  I always knew I could run my own business but never thought it would happen – yet here I am. 

I feel like my whole life was preparing me for an amazing life after 40 and now it’s time to come up with some new dreams. 

I guess what I am trying to say is this:

Dare to dream - and dream big because sometimes you are given everything you asked for, so you might as well make it good.

WYATT’S FAVORITE BEEF TIPS

Wyatt’s been asking for his “favorite food” for days now.  From the time he was a baby he has LOVED beef tips.  He’d have it all over his face, up his nose, and in his ears back then 😆. I’m linking the recipe and I’ll note it here, too.  I use half the salt because I use full salt soy and I also simmer for waaaaaay more hours than indicated.  Just keep adding water so it doesn’t burn. 

https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/23923/beef-tips/

3 tablespoons vegetable oil
1 onion, chopped
2 pounds cubed beef stew meat
2 cups water
1/4 cup soy sauce
1/4 cup Worcestershire sauce
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1 teaspoon salt (I use half)
1 teaspoon ground black pepper
1 (.75 ounce) packet dry brown gravy mix
1 cup water

In a large skillet heat oil over high heat. Saute the onion until almost translucent.

Add the stew meat and cook on high heat until meat is browned on all sides; about 3 to 5 minutes.

Pour 2 cups water, soy sauce, and Worcestershire sauce into the skillet. Stir in garlic powder, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

Meanwhile combine the gravy mix with 1 cup water. Mix thoroughly and stir into the meat mixture. Bring to a boil stirring frequently until slightly thickened.

node.text: Beau is finally feeling a lot better.  I was so worried about him.  On Sunday he was swimming one minute and then curled up in a ball in the side of the pool deck the next.  We convinced him to move to a chair outside where he slept under a towel.  He moved inside after a few hours and he slept most of the rest of the day, and all night.  On Monday I was able to get him into the pediatrician for a COVID and strep. Both tests were negative.  We’re giving him some time on the nebulizer because he was having some breathing difficulties with all of the mucus.  His fever has passed, so he’ll likely be back to school tomorrow… depending on how his cough is doing.  At this point he’s missed as many school days as he has attended this school year. 🤦🏻‍♀️

In a world where you can be anything – 𝐁𝐄 𝐊𝐈𝐍𝐃!

It’s so important to me to raise the triplets understanding this basic concept.

I’m having a bit of a rough day today.  Choosing to have a public account opens you to all sorts of people.  Many people feel that behind the veil of social media it’s okay to say things that they would never say to me directly. 

I struggle a bit because I was taught that if you have nothing nice to say you should choose to say nothing at all.  How this translates to social media is that I don’t go to other people’s pages and criticize their parenting, how they choose to spend their money, or what they choose to wear. 
✨𝘠𝘰𝘶 𝘬𝘯𝘰𝘸 𝘸𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘐 𝘥𝘰 𝘸𝘩𝘦𝘯 𝘐 𝘢𝘮 𝘴𝘤𝘳𝘰𝘭𝘭𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘐 𝘥𝘰𝘯’𝘵 𝘭𝘪𝘬𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘥𝘳𝘦𝘴𝘴 𝘺𝘰𝘶’𝘳𝘦 𝘸𝘦𝘢𝘳𝘪𝘯𝘨? 
𝘐 𝘬𝘦𝘦𝘱 𝘰𝘯 𝘴𝘤𝘳𝘰𝘭𝘭𝘪𝘯𝘨. 
✨𝘠𝘰𝘶 𝘬𝘯𝘰𝘸 𝘸𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘐 𝘥𝘰 𝘪𝘧 𝘐 𝘢𝘮 𝘴𝘤𝘳𝘰𝘭𝘭𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘐 𝘭𝘪𝘬𝘦 𝘺𝘰𝘶𝘳 𝘥𝘳𝘦𝘴𝘴? 
𝘐 𝘥𝘰𝘶𝘣𝘭𝘦 𝘵𝘢𝘱 𝘵𝘰 𝘵𝘦𝘭𝘭 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘵𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘐 𝘭𝘪𝘬𝘦 𝘪𝘵.  

Today a follower told me that I can’t take constructive criticism.  She did her mic drop and then blocked me so I couldn’t even reply.  I just don’t understand that kind of behavior.  Sarcasm is not constructive criticism (I just double checked with Wikipedia 😉).

I started this account as a way to share our journey.  I never envisioned triplets would be in my future.  I loved the nature versus nurture argument when I was in school and I enjoy sharing so you can see for yourself as you get to know the triplets.  It’s been an amazing journey so far. ✨ 𝘐𝘧 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘸𝘢𝘯𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘤𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘢𝘣𝘰𝘶𝘵 𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘯𝘨𝘴 – 𝘓𝘦𝘵’𝘴 𝘥𝘰 𝘪𝘵! ✨ I am available on DM.  But please (not just on my account) think twice before you put someone on blast.  There is likely a mama behind that screen who is making tough decisions all day long. 

✨ 𝐉𝐔𝐒𝐓 𝐁𝐄 𝐊𝐈𝐍𝐃! ✨

We wrapped up the first week of in person school with all 3 getting sick.  I expected it, as they haven’t been around too many other children to have a strong immunity built up.

Beau had a slight fever last night and all 3 are now coughing and congested.  I kept them home from school today, but the school nurse called and said that due to their symptoms they can’t come back until they have a negative COVID test and no cough.  It’s clearly going to be a few days until they can return to school no matter what the test results show. 

Here’s to a speedy recovery and a negative test result. 🤞🏻.

I might look like I am surrounded by a trio of cuties but they sure can get up to some shenanigans.  My feed is for all the cute pics, but my story will show you the REAL us. If you haven’t stopped by in a while – you should go take a peek.  In the past 24 hours I’ve posted about Savannah’s wannabe boyfriend and Beau’s wardrobe malfunction. 

As an update on Savannah’s current relationship status – I have come to learn that Vincent is a bit of a player.  The day before he told Savannah he had a crush on her he apparently had a crush on another girl.  First grade love is rather fleeting 😂. 

Side note - I have heard from a couple of you that our posts aren’t showing up in your feed.  Make sure to like/comment or go click on our story so you continue to see all the triplet cuteness.  If you don’t show the love, Instagram thinks you no longer want to see our posts.
